{
  "stem": "19550.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 224.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "I mean, there was a Jewish barber shop, or several of them.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And I don't think that you could go to a non-Jewish barber shop.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "I don't even know whether there was in existence.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "Or a corsetier-- it was all Jewish and Jewishly-owned.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The language of commerce was-- and, and the language of the street was, of course, Hungarian.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You have to know that the Hungarians were very insistent on Hungarianizing, not unlike the situation that we are familiar with here, although quite a number of the-- certainly, the more ultra-Orthodox Jews were very weak in their spoken Hungarian.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And some of them had no written Hungarian at all.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But by and large, of course, everybody spoke on Hungarian on the streets and on the-- and in, in the stores and workshops, including the Hasidic Jews who-- some of whom were merchants and who had to serve consumers and the clientele with what-- whatever Hungarian they could manage.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Or they had employees who, of course, who spoke Hungarian much better.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because by and large, sales personnel were not the people who went to cheder or, or to yeshiva.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So they were more, shall I say, worldly.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] But this-- this dynastic and self-perpetuating and kind of self-contained economy was really one of the main characteristics of the Jewish community in Kisvarda and certainly of other communities, too-- perhaps not to the same degree.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "On the other hand, it wasn't only-- the Jews obviously did not restrict themselves to their own community in their commerce and in their trade so that institutions or, or enterprises that were of a more general nature, may have been in-- not may have been-- actually were in Jewish hands.",
      "word_count": 51
    }
  ],
